<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">March 31, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-31-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-251704 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-28-at-4.26.24 PM-150x150.png" alt="Arthur" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://reactormag.com/a-lost-bit-of-the-story-of-merlin-and-arthur-has-been-found-at-cambridge/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">A lost piece of the story of Merlin and Arthur</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://countercraft.substack.com/p/what-we-write-about-when-we-write" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">What we write about when we write about writers</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2025/03/27/books/great-gatsby-100.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The many lives of </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">The Great Gatsby</span></i></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-31-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
